Tenth Ave., at the S.W. corner of Wost 41st Street. The R.C. Church of St. Raphael is shown on 41st Street west of Tenth Ave.
May 21, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
A one-story automobile service station will displace the three tenements (Nos.547-551 ) at the corner shown. These were erected in 1870 by the grandfather of the seller, John Muller. See the New York
Times of April 28, 1939 for further details.
